Privacy Policy
Noa provides this Privacy Policy to help you make an informed decision about whether to use or continue using the Noa Service. If you do not agree to our practices, please do not use the Noa Service.
This Privacy Policy is incorporated into and is subject to the Noa Terms and Conditions of Use. Your use of the Noa Service and any personal information you provide on the Noa Service remains subject to the terms of this Privacy Policy and our Terms and Conditions of Use.
1. Definitions
Before you continue we would like you to familiarise yourself with the following definitions in order to help you understand each of the terms detailed on this document. For all items not listed in this section, we will define their definition in the body of the text in a clear and concise manner.
"Content" :
Refers to any material(s) distributed as part of the Noa Service, including those which are text, graphic, numeric, video, or audio based.
"Customer" or "user" or "you" :
Refers to any anyone registering or subscribing to, or making use of, the Noa Service.
"Enterprise Subscriber":
Refers to a user who is granted access to the Noa Service as a result of payment made on their behalf by an organisation, as part of a group subscription.
"Noa" or "we" or "our":
Refers to Noa News Limited, a company registered in Ireland under company registration number 564767 and all subsidiaries and affiliates acting on behalf of Noa News Limited. A list of subsidiaries and affiliates are available upon request by using the contact form on our website.
"Noa Service" or "Service" :
Refers to the provisioning of Content to Customers across Noa’s smartphone and tablet applications, audio players, websites, and any other digital or non-digital offerings that may be available from time to time (collectively, the "Noa Site").
"Publisher" :
Refers to a publisher whose Content is distributed by Noa.
"Personal Information" :
Refers to any information that you, or an organisation or other party that pays for access to the Noa Service on your behalf, shares with Noa, that can be used to identify you (e.g. email addresses, name, place of residence, etc.) and any billing information that you provide to Noa. This also includes any data gathered by Noa as a result of your activity on the Service. This does not include any information that you provide to any third-party while using the Noa Service.
"Post" :
Any Content that users post, share, upload, and/or contribute to the Service.
"Subscriber":
Refers to a user who is granted access to the Noa Service as a result of direct payment from that user, or payment made on their behalf by another individual, by way of a gift.
"Subscription":
Refers to any subscription tier offered by Noa that provides access to the Noa Service, including group subscriptions.
"Subscription Period":
Refers to the length of a Subscription
"User Content":
Refers to comments, URLs or other links, messages, information, playlist compilations, and/or other types of content that you or other Noa users may Post.
2. Your consent
By the continued use of our Services or by becoming a Subscriber you consent to the use of your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
Please note that any User Content that users Post to the Noa Service becomes published content and is not considered personally identifiable information subject to this Privacy Policy.
3. What Does This Privacy Policy Cover?
This Privacy Policy is part of Noa Terms and Conditions of Use and covers the treatment of user information, including Personal Information, obtained by Noa, including information obtained when you access the Noa Service or any other application, website, or software provided by Noa.
This Privacy Policy does not apply to the practices of companies that Noa does not own or control, or to individuals whom Noa does not employ or manage, including any of the third parties to which Noa may disclose user information as set forth in this Privacy Policy.
4. The Information Noa Collects
Noa may obtain the following types of information from or concerning you or your mobile phone device, PC, or tablet computer which may include Personal Information that can be used to identify you as specified below:
4.1 User Provided Information:
You provide certain Personal Information, such as your email address, name, age, billing details and mobile device information to Noa when choosing to participate in various uses of the Noa Service (whether as a non-paying or Subscriber user). This information is used by Noa to allow you to login, to ensure that content that is displayed is age suitable, for VAT purposes, and for the overall performance of the Service.
4.2 Log File Information & Cookies:
When you use the Noa Site, our servers automatically record certain information that your web browser sends whenever you visit any website. These server logs may include information such as your web request, Internet Protocol ("IP") address, browser type, browser language, referring / exit pages and URLs, platform type, number of clicks, domain names, landing pages, pages viewed and the order of those pages, the amount of time spent on particular pages, the date and time of your request. When you use the Noa Service, our servers may log certain information that our software application sends whenever (a) an article is listened to in part or in full and (b) an audio or display advertisement is served, including your devices country code, date and time stamps, and the duration of time that certain information is playing or displayed (collectively "Usage Data").
5. The Information Noa Does Not Collect
Noa does not collect or have access to any payment details that you may enter when purchasing a Subscription on the Noa Site. Instead this information is processed and stored by Stripe, Inc., a San Francisco, USA based online payments company.
6. How long do we keep your personal information?
We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes for which we collected it. Your personal data may be retained by us for a longer period if required by law. Some of your personal data may need to be retained because of circumstances such as a legal dispute or regulatory investigation, which would usually mean that a longer retention period is required.
