7. The Way Noa Uses Information
We use any information that you provide to us to operate, maintain, and provide to you the features and functionality of the Noa Service. In particular, your email address may be used to access additional features of the Noa Service. Any personally identifiable information or User Content that you voluntarily disclose on the Noa Service in a public forum becomes publicly available and may be collected and used by other users of the Noa Service – for this reason we advise caution when sharing Posts. We do not share your Personal Information (e.g. your email address or name) to any third-parties. We may send you Noa-related emails, but only ever as part of a specific program or feature for which you will have the ability to opt-in or opt-out. Such emails may include a daily or weekly newsletter or emails that detail new or existing in-app features or offers which we believe you may be interested in. We will also use your email address for non-marketing or administrative purposes (such as notifying you of major Noa Service changes or for customer service purposes). We may use certain non-personally-identifiable information (such as anonymous Usage Data, IP addresses, etc.) to improve the quality and design of the Noa Service and to create new features, promotions, functionality, and services by storing, tracking, and analysing user preferences and trends. We may use log file information to monitor individual and aggregate metrics such as total number of visitors, pages viewed, articles listened, for example.
8. When Noa Discloses Information
Other users of the Noa Service will not see any of your Personal Information.
If you are an Enterprise Subscriber, we will provide the organisation paying your subscription, with personal information for the purpose of billing and reporting.
If you register for the Noa Service with a social media account, we may share your social media account identification details with social media platforms in order to:
Promote subscriber’s engagement to ensure they get the most of their subscription;
Prevent subscription offers being targeted at existing subscribers on social media platforms.
Facilitate the creation of lookalike audiences to assist in targeted advertising on social media platforms.
We do not share your Personal Information (such as your email address, name, or date of birth) with any other third-party companies, organisations, or individuals. We will not sell your Personal Information to third-party companies, organisations, or individuals. We may share non-personally-identifiable information (such as anonymous Usage Data, referring/exit pages and URLs, platform types, number of clicks, etc.) with interested third-parties to assist them in understanding the usage patterns for certain content, services, advertisements, promotions, and/or functionality on the Noa Service. We may collect and release Personal Information and/or non-personally-identifiable information if required to do so by law, or in the good-faith belief that such action is necessary to comply with national or international law or respond to a court order, subpoena, or search warrant or equivalent, or where in our reasonable belief, an individual’s physical safety may be at risk or threatened. NOA ALSO RESERVES THE RIGHT TO DISCLOSE PERSONAL INFORMATION AND/OR NON-PERSONALLY-IDENTIFIABLE INFORMATION THAT NOA BELIEVES, IN GOOD FAITH, IS APPROPRIATE OR NECESSARY TO ENFORCE OUR TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF USE, TAKE PRECAUTIONS AGAINST LIABILITY, TO INVESTIGATE AND DEFEND ITSELF AGAINST ANY THIRD-PARTY CLAIMS OR ALLEGATIONS, TO ASSIST GOVERNMENT ENFORCEMENT AGENCIES, TO PROTECT THE SECURITY OR INTEGRITY OF THE NOA SERVICE OR OUR SERVERS, AND TO PROTECT THE RIGHTS, PROPERTY, OR PERSONAL SAFETY OF NOA, OUR USERS OR OTHERS.
9. Your Choices and Rights
You may, of course, decline to submit Personal Information through the Noa Service, in which case Noa may not be able to provide certain of our Services to you. If you do not agree with our Privacy Policy or Terms and Conditions of Use please discontinue use of the Noa Service, delete your account (if applicable), and uninstall the Noa mobile or tablet application. Your continued usage of the Noa Service will signify your assent to and acceptance of our Privacy Policy and Terms and Conditions of Use.
You have certain rights regarding the personal data that we have about you; however, you should note that these rights can be subject to some exceptions:
Delete Data: You can ask us to erase or delete all or some of your personal data.
Change or Correct Data: You can ask us to change, update or fix your data in certain cases, particularly if it’s inaccurate.
Object to, or Limit or Restrict, Use of Data: You can ask us to stop using all or some of your personal data (e.g., if we have no legal right to keep using it) or to limit our use of it (e.g., if your personal data is inaccurate or unlawfully held).
Right to Access and/or Take Your Data: You can ask us for a copy of your personal data and can ask for a copy of personal data you provided in machine readable form.
Subscribers to our marketing mailing list can unsubscribe at any time by clicking the "unsubscribe" button within our emails.
Without prejudice to any other rights you may have, you may file a complaint with the Irish Data Protection Commissioner, which is our supervisory authority. You can contact the Commissioner at:
Canal House, Station Road, Portarlington, R32 AP23 Co. Laois Tel: 1890 252 231
www.dataprotection.ie
If you would like to exercise any of your rights or you have any questions about your rights please contact us using the contact form on our website, which is linked to below under term 14.
10. Third-party Advertisers
We hear you; online ads can be a real pain. At Noa we wanted to find a way to offer ads that were both user-friendly and
enjoyable to engage with
. And for those who would rather not engage, we wanted to ensure that any ads present on the Noa service did not take from your overall user experience. The simple fact of the matter is that producing high-quality journalism is a very expensive business. On the other hand, we don’t believe that you want to pay a colossal premium in order to consume such quality news, insight, and analysis. That’s why we have done our very best to provide ads that we ourselves are happy to consume. The benefit for all Subscribers and users is that the price of a Noa Subscription is greatly reduced as a result. Companies that advertise do help to keep the wheels of our economy in motion, so do think of them over similar sized rivals when making purchasing decisions.
There are two types of advertisements offered on the Noa Service. These are background display ads (as offered on the article play screen) and concise audio ads (as offered between articles from time-to-time) (the "Adverts"). In both instances Noa records and shares in aggregated form the Usage Data related to the Adverts with third-party advertising clients. Noa does not share any Personal Information with third-party advertisers. Any information shared with third-party advertisers is in an aggregated format and is strictly non-personally-identifiable.
We accept no responsibility for the content of advertising material, including any error, omission or inaccuracy contained within it.
11. Our Commitment to Data Security
Noa uses commercially reasonable physical, managerial, and technical safeguards to preserve the integrity and security of your Personal Information. We cannot, however, ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to Noa and you do so at your own risk. Using unsecured Wi-Fi or other unprotected networks to supply Personal Information to Noa is never recommended. Once we receive your transmission of information, Noa makes commercially reasonable efforts to ensure the security of our systems. However, please note that this is not a guarantee that such information may not be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed by breach of any of our physical, technical, or managerial safeguards. If Noa learns of a security systems breach, then we may attempt to notify you electronically so that you can take appropriate protective steps. Noa may post a notice on the Noa Site or through the Noa Service if a security breach occurs.
12. Special Note to International Users
The Noa Service is hosted in Ireland. If you are a user accessing the Noa Service from outside of the European Union, or any other region with laws or regulations governing personal data collection, use, and disclosure, that differ from European Union laws, please be advised that through your continued use of the Noa Services, which are governed by Irish law, this Privacy Policy, and our Terms and Conditions of Use, you are transferring your personal information to the European Union and you expressly consent to that transfer and consent to be governed by Irish law for these purposes.
13. In the Event of Merger, Sale, or Bankruptcy
In the event that Noa is acquired by or merged with a third party entity, we reserve the right to transfer or assign the information we have collected from our users as part of such merger, acquisition, sale, or other change of control. In the unlikely event of our bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganization, receivership, or assignment for the benefit of creditors, or the application of laws or equitable principles affecting creditors' rights generally, we may not be able to control how your Personal Information is treated, transferred, or used.
14. Changes and updates to this Privacy Notice
This Privacy Policy may be revised periodically and this will be reflected by the "effective date" above. Please revisit this document on the Noa website to stay aware of any changes. Your continued use of the Noa Service constitutes your agreement to this Privacy Policy and any amendments. This document is effective from 25
th
October 2018.
